The paper deals with object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a bidirectional RNN with attention, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new training target, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of contextual information and natural language processing techniques (such as attention) suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the subfields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM).
